HEADWORD: Simulacrum
<hw>Sim`u*la"crum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Simulacra</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. See
<er>Simulate</er>.]</ety> <def>A likeness; a semblance; a mock
appearance; a sham; -- now usually in a derogatory sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Beneath it nothing but a great <qex>simulacrum</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Thackeray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Simular</ent>⟦br⟧
